commit.message: Fix buffer overflow in zero'ing block (#171)

Adapt based on review feedback

Thank you, Marat, for the useful comments!

Fix x86 32 bit detection

When building on 32bit linux ("i386" architecture) on a 64 bit
machine, cmake will report CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR as x86_64 - which
is not intended. This currently causes NNPACK to detect x86-64
target when the psimd would be correct - the result is a mix of x86_64
and x86 object files and unhappy linkers.
This patch checks the pre-defined architecture macros for x86_32
and sets the backend to psimd if x86_32 is detected.
